result.execSummary:
The defendant Jim Nmi Lo was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Jim Nmi Lo is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Jim Nmi Lo was found guilty of Homicide by Negligent Operation/Vehicle, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.10(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superMiscConds.notes: Per C-31. Restitution is to be paid out of his prison wages at the rate of 25%. Once released on extended supervision the Defendant must obtain and maintain employment and make regular monthly payments. If payments are not made on a regular monthly basis, the Department of Corrections shall bring the matter before the court to order a specific payment schedule.

If probation or extended supervision is allowed to expire or is revoked with outstanding financial obligations, the supervising agent shall notify the court 10 days prior to the revocation or discharge and provide current financial information.  A civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for any balances due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect all debt.
Must not possess or consume controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.  Must not possess or consume alcoholic beverages.  Must not operate a motor vehicle without a valid driver's license.
